            <div class="field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field-item"><p>I recently did a webinar on using Python with IDEA and there seemed to be interest in a workshop on going more in depth on the subject. &nbsp;I have posted my thoughts on this workshop in the <a href="https://auditopia.com/groups/idea/forum/topic/using-python-with-idea-workshop/#post-204651">Auditopia</a> web site. &nbsp;If you are interested please feel free to leave a comment there.</p><hr><p>I recently did a webinar on Sampling with Caseware. &nbsp;If you are interested in viewing it you can see it from this link. &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gotostage.com/channel/e37586f5d3f74ac0a0fddb418f88265b/recording/ca7038dc63904fa2ac89d6da372123ef/watch">IDEA Sampling Webinar</a></p><hr><p>Hi everyone, I would just like to let everyone know that as of August 26, 2024 I will no longer be employed by Caseware. &nbsp;Currently I am hoping to keep this site going and I am hoping to stay in the IDEA universe by giving training and doing consulting work. &nbsp;If you have any IDEA projects that you could use my help with please contact me.</p><p>Thanks</p><p>Brian</p><hr><p>IDEAScripting.com is open for business again with a new look. &nbsp;There have been some changes to the site and there are more to come. &nbsp;Please read this post to get more details on what happened <a href="https://ideascripting.com/node/8578" title="IDEAScripting.com site update">IDEAScripting.com site update</a>.</p><hr><p>Welcome to IDEAScripting.com.&nbsp; I have set-up this site to support IDEA and IDEAScripting, which is the scripting language used by IDEA.</p><p>On the site I have made available some of my scripts that will hopefully help you out in your use of IDEA.&nbsp; I also have IDEAScript snippets that are short pieces of code that I continually reuse in my scripts.&nbsp; There are also several videos, including a series on how to create a simple IDEAScript.&nbsp; I am continually adding items as I have time to create them.</p><p>There is a forum where members can ask questions or post comments.&nbsp; In there I also have several custom functions that can be downloaded and used within IDEA.</p><p>I hope you enjoy the site and all comments are welcome.</p><p>Thanks</p><p>Brian</p></div>

</section>

</article>

    <div class="field__label">Background</div>
              <div class="field-item"><p>A small script that allows you to do an extraction based on a date. &nbsp;This script has been rewritten in Python.</p></div>
          </div>

  <div class="field field--name-field-documentation field--type-text-with-summary field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Documentation</div>
              <div class="field-item"><p>This script allows you to do an extraction based on a date.&nbsp; You select the file, the date field and then select the date from a calendar.&nbsp; You also can decide on the type of extract, do you only want equal dates, earlier dates, later date, the script gives you the option.</p><div>

  <div class="field field--name-field-background field--type-text-with-summary field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Background</div>
              <div class="field-item"><p>This script will create an number field that keeps a count based on the selected field.&nbsp; When the contents of the field change it resets to 0 and starts the count over.&nbsp; There is also a second script that will order the field based on a date field.</p></div>
          </div>

  <div class="field field--name-field-documentation field--type-text-with-summary field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Documentation</div>
              <div class="field-item"><p>This script will create an number field that keeps a count based on the selected field.&nbsp; When the contents of the field change it resets to 0 and starts the count over.</p><p>To use this script you must select a file and a field to perform the count on.</p><p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="598" height="393"></p><p>Using the sales transaction file as an example and selecting the PROD_CODE as the field we get the following:</p><p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="303" height="349"></p><p>If we index the file by PROD_CODE you will see that the auto number changes with the contents of the PROD_CODE changes.</p><p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="294" height="386"></p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
          </div>

  <div class="field field--name-field-language field--type-list-string field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Language</div>

              <div class="field-item">IDEAScript</div>

<article data-comment-user-id="2" id="comment-4718" class="js-comment single-comment">
  
        <header class="comment-user-picture">

    </header>
    
  <div class="single-comment-body">
          
      <h3 class="single-comment-title"><a href="/comment/4718#comment-4718" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="en">Hi Pat,In SmartAnalyzer in…</a></h3>
      
    
    <div class="single-comment-meta">
      <span><span>Brian Element</span> Fri, 03/07/2025 - 07:03</span>
              <p class="visually-hidden">In reply to <a href="/comment/4713#comment-4713" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="en">Transaction number</a> by <span>PATKELL</span></p>
          </div> <!-- /.single-comment-meta -->

    <div class="single-comment-content">
      
            <div class="field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field-item"><p>Hi Pat,</p><p>In SmartAnalyzer in the utility app that you can download from Passport there is a Sequential Numbering app that might do what you are looking for. &nbsp;Here is the description of it. &nbsp;Let me know if you are looking for something different.</p><p>The Sequential Numbering utility creates a new SEQ_NUMBER field in the specified database that contains a sequential number based on a user-defined index. You can define up to eight fields for the index. When the transactions based on the index change, then the SEQ_NUMBER field is reset to 1.</p><p>The following is an example of the dataset: &nbsp;</p><p>JE_NO&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;DATE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TIME&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PERIOD&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>161&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7:17:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>161&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7:17:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>162&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>162&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>163&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>163&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>164&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-07-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:21:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>164&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-07-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:21:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>164&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-07-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:21:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>When the Sequential Numbering utility is run on the above dataset, with the JE_NO field defined in the index, the SEQ_NUMBER field is added that contains the generated sequential number for each item with the index. When the index value changes, the sequential number resets to 1.</p><p>JE_NO&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;DATE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TIME&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PERIOD&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SEQ_NUMBER&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>160&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-12-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5:55:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>161&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7:17:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>161&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7:17:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>162&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>162&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>163&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>163&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2009-01-03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18:24:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>164&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-07-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:21:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>164&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-07-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:21:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>164&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015-07-31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:21:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p></div>

              <div class="field-item"><p>A small script that will take an IDEA file and render it into two columns with one column being the header names and the second column being the data.</p></div>
          </div>

  <div class="field field--name-field-documentation field--type-text-with-summary field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Documentation</div>
              <div class="field-item"><p>This script will take an IDEA file and render it into a two column file. &nbsp;As an example, this file as four columns and three rows. &nbsp;The script will take the header names and put them in column 1 and the data into column 2.</p><div>
  
  
  <div class="field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-visually_hidden">
    <div class="field__label visually-hidden">Image</div>

</div>
          </div>

</div>
<p>The following is the dialog, in this dialog you need to select the IDEA file to be transformed, enter the two column names and give an output filename.</p><div>
  
  
  <div class="field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-visually_hidden">

</div>
          </div>

</div>
<p>The following will be the result.</p><div>

      <article data-history-node-id="3116" class="node node-type-ideascript-snippets node-promoted node-view-mode-full">

  

  <header class="node-header">
        <div class="node-submitted-details">
      <div class="node-user">

      <div class="node-date">
        <i class="icon-calendar" aria-hidden="true"></i> <span><time datetime="2020-12-28T09:01:47-05:00" title="Monday, December 28, 2020 - 09:01">Mon, 12/28/2020 - 09:01</time>
</span>
      </div>

  <div class="node-content">
    
            <div class="field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field-item"><p>I use the Type procedure that allows you to create a user-defined data type containing one or more elements.&nbsp; I create an element for each of piece of information that is contained in the field then I use this type as an array and populate it with all the field information.&nbsp; This is an easy way to get all the information on the fields in a database in a quick manner.</p></div>
      
  <div class="field field--name-field-snippet field--type-text-long field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Snippet</div>
              <div class="field-item"><pre><code>
Option Explicit

'create the type definition that will be used to hold the field information
Type Fields
	sName As String
	sDescription As String
	sType As String 'char for character, num for numeric, date for date, time for time
	iLength As Integer
	iDecimals As Integer
	sEquation As String
	bHasActionField As Boolean
	bIsImpliedDecimal As Boolean
	bIsVirtual As Boolean
	iTypeDetail As Integer 'see typeconstant for all types
End Type

Dim tFields() As Fields 'define the array to hold all the field information

Sub Main

	Call getFields("General Ledger-GL")
	Dim msg As String
	Dim i As Integer
	For i = 0 To UBound(tFields)
		msg = "Field Name: " &amp; tFields(i).sName &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Description: " &amp; tFields(i).sDescription &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Type: " &amp; tFields(i).sType &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Length: " &amp; tFields(i).iLength &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Decimals: " &amp; tFields(i).iDecimals &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Equation: " &amp; tFields(i).sEquation &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Has Action Field: " &amp; tFields(i).bHasActionField &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Implied Decimals: " &amp; tFields(i).bIsImpliedDecimal &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Virtual Field: " &amp;  tFields(i).bIsVirtual &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		msg = msg &amp; "Type Detail: " &amp; tFields(i).iTypeDetail &amp; Chr(13) &amp; Chr(10)
		MsgBox msg
	Next i
	
End Sub

Function getFields(sTempFilename As String)
	Dim db As database
	Dim table As table
	Dim field As field
	Dim count As Integer
	Dim i As Integer
	
	Set db = client.OpenDatabase(sTempFilename)
		Set table = db.TableDef
			count = table.count
			ReDim tFields(count - 1) 
			For i = 1 To count
				Set field = table.GetFieldAt(i)
				tFields(i - 1).sName= field.name
				tFields(i - 1).sDescription = field.description
				If field.IsCharacter Then
					tFields(i - 1).sType = "char" 
				ElseIf field.IsNumeric Then
					tFields(i - 1).sType = "num"
				ElseIf field.IsDate Then
					tFields(i - 1).sType = "date"
				ElseIf field.IsTime Then
					tFields(i - 1).sType = "time"
				End If	
				tFields(i - 1).iLength = field.Length
				tFields(i - 1).iDecimals = field.Decimals
				tFields(i - 1).sEquation = field.Equation 
				tFields(i - 1).bHasActionField = field.HasActionField
				tFields(i - 1).bIsImpliedDecimal = field.IsImpliedDecimal
				tFields(i - 1).bIsVirtual = field.isVirtual
				tFields(i - 1).iTypeDetail = field.Type
			Next i
		Set table = Nothing
	Set db = Nothing
End Function
</code></pre></div>

              <div class="field-item"><pre><code>
Sub Main
	Dim sTime1 As String
	Dim sTime2 As String
	Dim iTimeDif As String
	Dim i As Long
	'start time
	sTime1 = Now()
	
	'run your code, loop is for demo purposes
	For i = 1 To 10000000
	Next i
	
	'end time
	sTime2 = Now()
	
	'get the time different in seconds
	iTimeDif = DateDiff("s", sTime1, sTime2)
	MsgBox "Time: " &amp; iTimeDif
End Sub
</code></pre></div>
